components.name: AppComponent
components.templateData:
Foundations
Empathy is our north star. We speak to a diverse customer base, so our goal is to create content that’s brief, useful, and accessible.
Our core values
TIAA’s Content Design System (CDS) provides consistent, clear and professional written communication. The CDS serves as a trusted reference tool for content strategists ensuring that our content maintains a unified voice and effectively communicates TIAA’s identity and message by observing the following:
Clarity
By providing guidelines on grammar, usage, and formatting. Consistent language and structure reduce ambiguity and improve understanding.
Brand identity
Verbal brand is more than the sum of usage, punctuation, and grammar. The CDS is the single source of truth for our brand's voice, tone, and identity across all TIAA channels.
Efficiency
The CDS serves as a handy default for resolving grammatical, syntactical and usage uncertainties about content standards.
Professionalism
Adhering to a style guide demonstrates professionalism and attention to detail. It ensures that written materials meet high-quality standards, enhancing the credibility of the content and the organization.
Principles
Embrace mobile-first language design Shorter copy works best on mobile screens. Keep word-count low and use concise language.
Commit to platform agnosticism Make sure your copy makes sense wherever a customer sees it.
Aim for clarity and scannability Readers tend to scan text. Make sure they can grasp the essence of a screen at a glance.

components.name: PageComponent
components.template:
Pages in Storybook

We recommend building UIs with a component-driven process starting with atomic components and ending with pages.

Render pages with mock data. This makes it easy to build and review page states without needing to navigate to them in your app. Here are some handy patterns for managing page data in Storybook:

  • Use a higher-level connected component. Storybook helps you compose such data from the "args" of child component stories
  • Assemble data in the page component from your services. You can mock these services out using Storybook.

Get a guided tutorial on component-driven development at Storybook tutorials . Read more in the docs .

Tip Adjust the width of the canvas with the Viewports addon in the toolbar
